    Scope and Contents
Sandretto, Italian immigrant, discusses coming to the U.S., Depression, factory work during WWII, life in Henderson and Gillespie, Illinois, coal mining and the Progressive Miners during the mine wars of the 1930's. She also discusses family photo albums and genealogy. 3 tapes, 270 mins. 
Interview by Michael E. Alepra, 1991 
